reviews.review_text:
Nice recording of  a good show Joe D'Amico does a really nice job of recording shows and this one is no exception. The opening Iko Iko is fun while Little Red Rooster is it's usual self. Brown-Eyed Women is where the show really gets going for me. The only (known) GD version of Fever is next and is well played. Stagger Lee and When I Paint My Masterpiece are fun versions while the closing Bird Song->Promised Land end the set strong.

The second set gets off to a very strong start with Scarlet->Fire. The Playing In The Band->Drums->Space->The Other One->Stella Blue->Throwing Stones->Good Lovin'->La Bamba->Good Lovin' jam is well played and it's nice to see Throwing Stones going into something other than Not Fade Away. Knockin' On Heaven's Door is a good encore.
